{
  "question_id": "347c61ab-8444-4606-be54-825111fd4ea1",
  "short_text": "Square (For Loop)",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints a **Square** of `N` rows and `N` columns using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n* * *\r\n* * *\r\n* * *\r\n```\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\n* There is a space after every star(`*`).\r\n* Use **For** loop.\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows and `N` columns containing stars (`*`) as a **Square** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\r\n\r\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **4** rows and **4** columns as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/square.png' widthPercent='65'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image, there is a space after every star(`*`).\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n* * * *\r\n* * * *\r\n* * * *\r\n* * * *\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "8cb91253-62ae-40c2-8fec-c5cc30e98f0c",
      "code_content": "number_of_rows = int(input())\n\nfor i in range(number_of_rows):\n    print(\"* \" * number_of_rows)\n",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
